It has some issues. I'm totally fine with spending 30 seconds to open a chest by watching an ad. The chests sometimes have crap stuff like 100 gold, but most of the time it's ok and I don't mind. What I DO mind, is when ads start popping up after games that you didn't pick up a chest in. Even worse, sometimes ads play when you try to unpause the game. You can skip these ads after a few seconds, but it's still really irritating. 
The other issue I have is character balance. Once you get past the castle, the only characters (and I have them all) that I find useful are Werewolf, Amazon, Warlock, and probably Wizard but I haven't tried him yet. Everyone else lacks the ability generation to backflip as often as you need to in order to get enough kills and avoid hazards. Also the monk's special is horrible.

The game is a relatively enjoyable mobile game - mindless diversion; a time killer when you need a break from other things. However, the whole watch ads to unlock chests is a huge negative - a 30 second full screen video ad to open a chest that gives a few coins or differently colored pixels for a character is overkill (there is a time limited XP bonus too). Video and other full screen ads appear at random (although turning on airplane mode is an easy way around having ads display, you just can't unlock any chests). With all due respect to the developers, the game just isn't good enough relative to the intrusive and frequent ads. Yes, the chest ads are opt in but the game is major grinding without opening chests. Even with chests, it's major grinding. $4 to remove ads is about $2 too high, particularly since there are a lot of other games that offer so much more content for the same or less money.

This is a really fun game, but I have one major and one minor complaint.

Major complaint: You need a way to turn the sound off! I realize I can turn the music off, butunless I'm missing itthe SFX are always on and very loud. And it isn't enough to turn the sound off on my phone because when I'm listening to music through my headphones I can't control that. My commute is where I get most of my time to play games, and and I simply can't play this one with the sound problem.

Minor complaint: When I started my second character, I was a little surprised to find out that it had a different move set and wasn't just a cosmetic change. Perhaps a preview of what the abilities are to better let players decide which character(s) they may want to buy first.
